til 2017. Posterior\nprobabilities of transect allocations to the same cluster substantially\nincrease through time showing a potential homogenization of community\ncomposition across the whole GBR. The Bayesian model highlights the diversity\nof coral reef community composition within a coral reef and rapid changes\nacross large spatial scales that may contribute to undermining the future of\nthe GBR's biodiversity.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 5 May 2021 15:47:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-05-06"}
